Most difficult place to fight lazy must be Goa 😋but you got to be 💪🏽 for just that minute, at least !!!!! Big thank you to that tree for being there, and the crows don’t sound happy, but you gotta do what you gotta do !!!! That’s life ❤️
.
.
.
#health #love #life #happiness #goa #pullups #trees #fightlazylifelong

How much should you exercise ? Most common question 😀 For me the answer to how much and what depends purely on the objective of the exercise, why are you doing it ? 
.
.
.
For me the goal is to maintain a level of fitness, based on performance more than looks, a level that allows me to just get up and do whatever I want in my life :) I exercise 15min EVERY DAY 😊
.
.
.
Whatever your goal and whatever the exercise, make sure you start really slow, increase gradually and most importantly, be regular. Fight Lazy ! Every day is a learning experience about your mind and body. The only limits are what you choose !
.
.
.
What is your goal ??
.
.
#health #happiness #life #love #fightlazylifelong

#paidpartnership
I like pushing boundaries & testing new limits in search of incredible, and that's how I found #ASUS8z. 
Perfect for my active lifestyle, it's #BigOnPerformanceCompactInSize !
Catch me at the launch of this marvel on 28th February at 12 PM 😀

Head to @asusindia's bio & set a reminder!

The easiest way to fight lazy is to find different, fun movements :) swinging the mugdar in horse stance is something new for me ! Once i have built and maintained some basic fitness, combining muscular strength and mobility, its easier to choose fun exercises to try whenever you have the time 😀 and if you spend a 10-15min on yourself every day, you can only get better!
.
.
.
For me, its never been important to have a workout routine or regime, its all about being active and exploring my body's capability whenever I get a chance 🙂
.
.
#fightlazylifelong #health #happiness #love #life #horsestance

Pullup variation !!
Some people find it difficult to believe that i exercise for a total of 15-20min every day 😀 but I find that this much is enough to enable me to be fit enough to do the things I want in my life. One set each of 4-5 different exercises at different times during the day. A 5min plank, one set of 50 pushups, one set on the pull up bar, one set on the parallel bar, 2min swinging a mugdal or throwing a kettlebell, whatever seems like fun at that moment ! 
.
.
.
Being fit is easy if you know your goal and make it a priority 😊
.
.
.
#health #love #life #happiness 📸 @ankita_earthy

latestPosts.caption: Fun week in England with @ankita_earthy 😀 ABBA concert, seven sisters hike, lots of great food and of course, the most exciting Wimbledon men’s single’s final on centre court ! Been watching Wimbledon right from the earliest days of tv in the 1970’s, with players like Bjorn Borg and John McEnroe, Boris Becker, Martina Navratilova, so actually being here live was really like being a part of something historic, especially with Jannik Sinner being the first Italian to ever win in almost 150 years 🤩 I’ve been to world level sporting events before, but the energy and the excitement of centre court at Wimbledon really is something to be experienced 😀

Endurance athlete, wellness icon, and Bazaar India’s June-July cover star Milind Soman (@milindrunning) has never played by the rules of age. “At 20, you don’t understand ageing. But as you get older, you begin to understand more about change—your mind, the way you perceive the world, your body, your ideas change, even what you want from life changes. So does the gratitude you have and the understanding that if you want to keep this for the rest of your life, you need to work consistently at it.”

Read the full cover story at the link in bio.

latestPosts.caption: Mumbai to Goa day 4 - hills and rain, hills and rain, hills and rain and wind😀body feels like it has adapted to the routine of 90km cycling and 20km running 😀 only through challenges like this can you understand and celebrate the amazing strength of the human mind, body and spirit. And through that understanding, enjoy life to the full! #FitIndianRun #Mumbai2Goa

Day 2&3 just hills, hills, hills 😬 ghat pe ghat, ghat pe ghat, to paraphrase an old dialogue 😜 90km cycling and 20km running for 3 consecutive days so far, feels amazing !! Lots of  pushups for selfies .. meeting fitter Indians on the way 😀 people often ask me, Kyu karte ho itna, Marna hi toh hai - but I think if I haven’t explored the limits of the potential of mind and body at every age, I haven’t really lived or shown gratitude for the amazing gifts I have recieved from the almighty😀 #fitindianrun #mumbai2goa

400 mg of Shilajit resin, infused with honey that can support improved stamina and long-lasting energy.

Fit Indian run started today ! 5 days, 600km, Mumbai to Goa 😀 made it more fun this time, doing the half iron man distances for running and cycling every day, 90km cycling and 21km running 🤪 with the best crew @ankita_earthy of course who is doing the running segment with me as well ! This kind of challenge is something I do once a year, just to make sure that everything is working properly 😛 some people tell me it’s inspiring them to do better, and to get fitter so they can enjoy life more, so that’s the icing on the cake 🎂 May every Indian be a Fit Indian, Jai Hind !!!! @fitindiaoff
